				<li id="16572446" class="cmnt-root" data="77" data-d="1648431745000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579670/Golden-Scarab" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">27 Mar 2022 21:42</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16572446" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I&apos;ve done some testing on how it specifically stacks with the gold-pickled Fowl foot:<br/><br/>Killing one non hostile albinauric near the grace: Palace Approach Ledge Road with no rune boosting effects gave me 2453 Runes<br/>This means that with the Gold Scarab, it should be 2943; this was indeed the case.<br/>In the next run I added the gold pickled fowl foot, the result was 3826 runes per kill.<br/>We know that 2453*1.5 = 2679.5 so this suggests the buffs stack multiplicatively, and the math for that checks out:<br/><br/>(2453*1.2)*1.3 = 3826.68, upon testing: killing one neutral albinauric with both buffs active gave me 3826 Runes.<br/><br/>Conclusion: Rune acquisition buffs stack multiplicatively, and Rune gain is rounded down to whole numbers</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16572446" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16572446" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="